This table, a rather comprehensive overview, presents the real [hydrogen-like wave functions](/Wave_function) for all [atomic orbitals](/Atomic_orbital) extending up to 7s. Consequently, it encompasses all occupied orbitals found in the ground state of every element currently known in the [periodic table](/Periodic_table), up to and including [radium](/Radium). The "ψ" graphs are meticulously rendered, with the negative and positive phases of the [wave function](/Wave_function) clearly distinguished by two different colors (arbitrarily, but consistently, red and blue). The p<sub>z</sub> orbital is, in essence, identical to the p₀ orbital. However, the p<sub>x</sub> and p<sub>y</sub> orbitals are not fundamental eigenstates but rather formed by taking [linear combinations](/Linear_combination) of the p<sub>+1</sub> and p<sub>-1</sub> orbitals (which explains why they are grouped under the *m* = ±1 label). It's also worth noting that the p<sub>+1</sub> and p<sub>-1</sub> orbitals do not share the same shape as the p₀ orbital, as they represent pure [spherical harmonics](/Spherical_harmonics) with distinct angular dependencies.

